{SOUTH opens 2♣ with her balanced 22 points.

NORTH has 8 points AND a 5-card ♠ suit. This is strong enough for a positive response, so

he bids 2♠.

SOUTH completes the description of her hand by saying 2NT.

NORTH does NOT rebid the ♠s; his first bid already promised a 5-card suit. He just

bids 3NT.}
